<refnamediv><refname>prependpath</refname><refpurpose>add a dir to a path environment variable then chain</refpurpose></refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
<cmdsynopsis>
<command>prependpath</command> 
<arg choice='req'><replaceable>var</replaceable></arg> 
<arg choice='req'><replaceable>dir</replaceable></arg> 
<arg choice='req'><replaceable>next-prog</replaceable></arg>
</cmdsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection><title>Description</title>

<para>
<command>prependpath</command> is a chain-loading utility that prepends the value <replaceable>dir</replaceable> to the path environment variable <replaceable>var</replaceable>, and then chain loads to <replaceable>next-prog</replaceable> with the <citerefentry><refentrytitle>execvp</refentrytitle><manvolnum>3</manvolnum></citerefentry> function.  
If the environment variable is set and not empty, it inserts a colon (<code>:</code>) between the prepended <replaceable>dir</replaceable> and the old value of <replaceable>var</replaceable>.
</para>

<para>
<replaceable>next-prog</replaceable> may contain its own command line options, which <command>prependpath</command> will ignore.
</para>

